s rise to the inferior thyroid artery","The thyrocervical trunk gives rise to the superior thyroid artery"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eexternal carotid artery gives rise to the superior thyroid artery\u003C/strong\u003E as its first branch. This vessel then descends along the external surface of the thyroid cartilage to supply the superior aspect of the thyroid gland.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EThe internal carotid artery gives rise to the superior thyroid artery\u003C/strong\u003E - The internal carotid artery has no branches in the neck\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EThe subclavian artery directly gives rise to the inferior thyroid artery\u003C/strong\u003E - The inferior thyroid artery arises from the thyrocervical trunk, which is a branch of the subclavian artery\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EThe common carotid artery gives rise to the inferior thyroid artery\u003C/strong\u003E - The common carotid artery typically has no branches before its bifurcation\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EThe thyrocervical trunk gives rise to the superior thyroid artery\u003C/strong\u003E - The thyrocervical trunk gives rise to the inferior thyroid artery\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EVascular anatomy is important during thyroid surgery where careful dissection and ligation of these vessels is required.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The superior thyroid artery is the first branch of the external carotid artery and supplies the superior portion of the thyroid gland.","The inferior thyroid artery arises from the thyrocervical trunk of the subclavian artery and supplies the inferior portion of the thyroid gland.","The arterial supply of the thyroid gland forms rich anastomoses between vessels from both sides, providing collateral circulation."],"references":["Netter FH. Netter Atlas of Human Anatomy: A Regional Approach with Latin Terminology. Eighth edition. Elsevier; 2022","Dalley AF, Agur AMR. Moore\u2019s Clinically Oriented Anatomy. International edition. Lippincott Williams \u0026 Wilkins; 2022","Drake R. Gray\u2019s Atlas of Anatomy. 3rd ed. Elsevier Health Sciences; 2021"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"62454"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17344"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"62454","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/62454"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-05T20:49:42+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-05T20:50:39+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10034"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"76949"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"typ